title: 820-3208 not turning on
message:
Hey info, this mac suffered oxidation on the components Q7830, U6100, U5010, U3890 and Q9706. I replaced the oxidized components, but the fan speeds up and stops.

title: 820-3208 not turning on
message:
Any pulse at R7831?
Check for short there.

Check akk SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and their traces.
Clean/remove J6100.

title: 820-3208 not turning on

40mV, pulse 3.186V
removed.
I checked the resistor values, they are ok.

title: 820-3208 not turning on
message:
You must check all the traces between these resistors.
Some of them are in the other side, or faraway under PCH area.
Did you remove J6100?

Try known good BIOS.
Heat PCH with quality flux.
